structure.unit: GENERAL PROVISIONS CONCERNING CRIMES AND PUNISHMENTS

law.text: The warden of the penitentiary shall make due return, on the copy of the judgment of the court pronouncing the death sentence, of the manner, time and place of its execution by him. The return shall be filed by the clerk of the court in the papers of the case in his office.
law.history: Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 1137-5.
